IT was supposed to be a day of joy and celebration, but it turned tragic for Durban twin brothers. IPSS Medical Rescue’s Dylan Meyrick says they responded to a complex in Shaka’s Rock after the collapse of a third-story balcony rail. “Upon arrival, it was found that three people had been on the balcony at the time of collapse and were all in critical condition,” Meyrick said in a statement. He added that IPSS Medical Rescue’s advanced life support and paramedics worked to stabilise the patients. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments “Unfortunately, both were declared deceased. The third patient was taken to a nearby facility,” he said. 